Suspected herdsmen yesterday afternoon attacked Div-Nzaav community in Kwande local government area of Benue State and killed a farmer as wells as abducted two women and children. The attack came barely two weeks after armed herdsmen attacked some communities in Guma local government area, during a wake-keep and killed seven mourners. The marauders attempted to rape two wives of the traditional ruler of the community. LEADERSHIP gathered that the community has been deserted by the villagers, who have taken refuge in the market at Jato-aka. A source in Kwande, who is an indigene of Div-Nzaav community, Mr. Solomon Amande, explained that the armed herders came into the village last Friday and camped in a nearby swamp before they unleashed mayhem yesterday on the community. He said: “The suspected herdsmen who were shooting sporadically in the air entered the first compound and met one Tarfa Simon and shot him to death, while a young woman identified as Ngusonun Kighir who was making garri in the compound was also macheted. “On sighting Simon, they shot him to death and macheted Ngusonun, they also abducted two women with children to an unknown destination. “As I talk to you, we have recovered the corpse of Simon while Ngusonun is currently receiving medical treatment at a clinic in Jato-aka in Kwande. We have reported the attack to the Divisional Police Station in Kwande and the police post in Turan Jato-aka. “Year-in-year-out, we are being attacked and killed by armed herdsmen. I am appealing to state and federal governments to create a special camp for our people since no one could go into the community to reside,” Amande lamented. When contacted,  the Benue State command police public relations officer, DSP Catherine Anene, said that she was yet to get details of the fresh attack in the area.  